  "_notes": {
    "scope_limitation": "Backtest uses BACKTEST_WEIGHTS (sr/gap/momentum/ma/structure/vix only) because Kite's REST API cannot reconstruct point-in-time option-chain snapshots for arbitrary past dates -- PCR/OI/basis are fully live in production (signal.py/futures.py) but untested here.",
    "trade_plan_fix": "An R:R bug was found and fixed during this milestone: target1 previously used the nearest S/R level (often very close), while the stop used a much wider 1x ATR -- 100% of planned trades had R:R < 1.0 (median 0.21) before the fix. build_trade_plan now floors the target at k_target/k_stop (2.0) and only extends it when real S/R sits genuinely further out.",
    "honest_state": "Post-fix, directional accuracy sits near 50% and expectancy is still negative for both instruments -- the raw rule-based swing engine (without PCR/OI) shows no validated edge yet on 2yr of history. This is the expected state of a first-pass model before weight optimization (M6) and before the live PCR/OI/basis factors (which ARE working, see M1/M3) are exercised forward by the paper-trading ledger.",
    "regime_adaptive_rsi": "Hypothesis: momentum_subscore treated RSI as trend-following everywhere, but a real-data spot check (see M2) showed BankNifty in a range regime (ADX 13.7) where high RSI means overbought/due-to-revert, not bullish continuation. Wired ADX+VIX regime classification (built in M3, never actually used) into signal.py so RSI reads as mean-reversion in range regimes. Honest result: BankNifty improved modestly (dir_acc 50.6%->52.1%, profit_factor 0.81->0.87), Nifty got slightly worse (dir_acc 45.0%->44.3%, profit_factor 0.44->0.39) -- a mixed, marginal effect, not a breakthrough. Kept the fix (it is theoretically correct regardless of this window's outcome) but deliberately stopped further ad-hoc single-shot tuning here to avoid overfitting to this one fixed 2yr window -- real optimization belongs in M6, tied to the paper-trading ledger's forward, out-of-sample results with drift caps."
  }
